-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Module: @(#)README	1.2     Date: 97/07/18
-- Author: Lester B. Knutsen  Email: lester@advancedatatools.com
--         Advanced DataTools Corporation
-- Discription:	This is a set of SQL scripts that use the sysmaster
-- 	database to provide information on the status of your server
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
blobfree.sql	- Displays number of free blob pages in blobspace
buffcach.sql	- Displays % of reads and writes from buffers
chkflist.sql	- Displays free space within a chunk
chkio.sql	- Displays chunk IO status
chkiosum.sql	- Displays chunk IO as percent of total IO 
chkstatus.sql	- Displays info and status for a chunk
dblist.sql	- Displays database list, owner, and logging status
dbsfree.sql	- Displays free space in all dbspaces like Unix "df -k " 
dbsfree72.sql	- Displays free space in all dbspaces like Unix "df -k " (7.2X)
dbwho.sh	- Shell Script to list database, user, and workstation 
dbwho.sql	- Displays who is using what database
getconfig.sql	- Displays effective configuration paramaters
keyprofile.sql	- Displays key server profile/perfomance statatics
locks.sql	- Displays locks, users and tables
lockwait.sql	- Displays only locks with other users waiting on them
logstat.sql	- Displays logical log status
sesprof.sql	- Displays user session profile info
session.sql	- Displays short list of user sessions
seswait.sql	- Displays session wait status
syssql.sql	- Displays users SQL statement
tabextent.sql	- Displays tables, number of extents, and size of table
tabextplan.sql	- Displays extents and proposed new extent sizes
tablayout.sql	- Displays tables and extents
tabprof.sql	- Displays table IO performance
txlogcnt.sql	- Displays how many open transactions are in each log
txlogpos.sql	- Displays users and position in logical logs
vpprof.sql	- Displays VP status
vpstat.sql	- Displays VP status like onstat -g sch
